Jarvis, and I went to school together. He was a year 
ahead of me in high school. But he was in the 11th

09:40.210 --> 09:45.057
Marines and I was in the 3rd Corps. We were together 
in China for most of those nine months. We both

09:51.060 --> 09:56.567
decided then that what we needed to do when we got 
out was go get an education. And both of us had come

09:57.227 --> 10:09.843
out of a small country school, and we didn't know a 
thing about what schools were what, which ones we

09:57.227 --> 10:09.843
should be interested in attending. We knew that we 
had to go to a state school. We couldn't afford

10:11.786 --> 10:13.508
anything else. We knew there would be a GI bill that 
would help us through. So we decided together

10:18.412 --> 10:26.921
that, well, it came down between University of 
Texas and Texas A&M. So we were in a bar one night and

10:26.941 --> 10:35.650
decided, well, we need to make up our minds where 
we're going to go. We said, OK, let's flip a coin.

10:37.692 --> 10:42.617
Head, heads, U-T, tails, this is A&M. Tales came up 
and we said, OK, there's where we're going. And so

10:46.545 --> 10:53.513
that was that was the great decision making that we 
did in great evaluation of all the options. Now,

10:53.593 --> 10:57.917
how far in advance of coming over here was that 
flip? Oh, that was about a month before we left.

11:00.941 --> 11:04.304
That had been in about June of 46. And we got back. He 
got a little ahead of me. He was already home when I

11:09.970 --> 11:11.912
got home in August. But from August until the first 
of September when school started here. And how did

11:18.887 --> 11:21.670
you get from home over here? Did you have a car? No. I 
was going to be surprised if you did. No, we neither

11:26.935 --> 11:28.157
had a car. So we, of course, we did have a sea bag. 
That's what we lived in for the last two or three

11:30.539 --> 11:32.802
years. So we each packed our sea bags up and got out 
and hitchhiked. Came down here and came into

11:41.575 --> 11:45.521
College Station, first time we'd ever been here or 
seen anything about it. We were quite, quite

11:45.582 --> 11:50.570
surprised really to see what was here. What did you 
bring in the sea bag? We brought our, primarily

11:53.455 --> 12:07.718
our, our work clothes are from the, from the Marine 
